Ship a minimal linux/nsfs.h for kernels that don't provide it.

systemd 257.x uses the Linux-specific NS_GET_OWNER_UID ioctl
(added in kernel 4.11) via <linux/nsfs.h>. The CoreELEC Amlogic-old
kernel (3.14-based) ships no nsfs.h at all, so the include fails.

Provide the header inside src/basic/linux/ — it sits on the local
include path (src/basic/) and will be found via #include <linux/nsfs.h>
since the directory is in systemd's include search path. When the
real kernel headers on the host/target do provide nsfs.h, the kernel
headers win because they come first; our file is the fallback.

diff --git a/src/basic/linux/nsfs.h b/src/basic/linux/nsfs.h
new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
+++ b/src/basic/linux/nsfs.h
@@ -0,0 +1,11 @@
+#ifndef _LINUX_NSFS_H
+#define _LINUX_NSFS_H
+
+#include <linux/ioctl.h>
+
+#define NSIO             0xb7
+#define NS_GET_USERNS    _IO(NSIO, 0x1)
+#define NS_GET_PARENT    _IO(NSIO, 0x2)
+#define NS_GET_NSTYPE    _IO(NSIO, 0x3)
+#define NS_GET_OWNER_UID _IO(NSIO, 0x4)
+#endif
